{"source_key":"sha256-afaa8c95f8efcc789cbf956996107b29","record_index":27,"record_hash":"sha256:538ec1ee8bcd54d6840418d7eddf7334e228722bca83b6ef305ba2f5e9367067","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:22:44.919Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: c77859\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1796\nOutput:\n    80\t\n    81\t```text\n    82\tbranch -> session -> records\n    83\t```\n    84\t\n    85\tBranches, changes, commits, and pull requests should still reference sessions or\n    86\tturns. They should not own transcript data.\n    87\t\n    88\t## What A Turn Means\n    89\t\n    90\tA session turn is the unit of \"what we observed this time.\"\n    91\t\n    92\tEvery time the capture flow runs:\n    93\t\n    94\t1. parse the transcript snapshot\n    95\t2. deduplicate against already stored record hashes\n    96\t3. append only new transcript records\n    97\t4. write a turn object describing this capture invocation\n    98\t5. record which transcript records belong to the turn\n    99\t6. record enough repository environment state to support later association\n   100\t\n   101\tCreate a session turn only when capture writes at least one new transcript\n   102\trecord. An environment-only observation should not create a turn. Otherwise the\n   103\tmodel drifts from agent-session capture into repository telemetry.\n   104\t\n   105\tThe first hook run for a session may capture more than one actual conversation\n   106\tturn if it imports an existing transcript backlog. Later stop-hook runs should\n   107\tusually map more closely to one user/agent interaction. That distinction should\n   108\tstay visible in the model: a turn is a capture observation, not necessarily a\n   109\tprovider-native turn.\n   110\t\n   111\tFor first-time backfill, create one capture turn containing all newly written\n   112\trecords and one environment snapshot from capture